WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.508 --> 00:00:04.599
It's an honor to minister to you right now
wherever you are, whether you're in your home

00:00:04.599 --> 00:00:06.008
or your car.

00:00:06.008 --> 00:00:09.918
Some people listen to me while they work out,
so that's good.

00:00:09.918 --> 00:00:13.179
Get another rep!

00:00:13.179 --> 00:00:14.179
That's your sign.

00:00:14.179 --> 00:00:16.079
You were praying for a sign that you should
work out today.

00:00:16.079 --> 00:00:17.079
This is it.

00:00:17.079 --> 00:00:18.079
Go work out.

00:00:18.079 --> 00:00:20.529
Thus saith the Lord.

00:00:20.529 --> 00:00:22.109
I want to share with you today…

00:00:22.109 --> 00:00:27.539
Let's go to Acts, chapter 3.

00:00:27.539 --> 00:00:33.329
As you're turning there, just to give a moment
for everybody to turn, put in the chat right

00:00:33.329 --> 00:00:40.759
now where you're joining us from…YouTube
or Facebook or wherever you're joining us

00:00:40.759 --> 00:00:42.179
from.

00:00:42.179 --> 00:00:43.908
Where are you joining us from?

00:00:43.908 --> 00:00:46.669
We want to know.

00:00:46.669 --> 00:00:50.859
And what's your name, what's your favorite
band, and what's your favorite flavor of ice

00:00:50.859 --> 00:00:52.569
cream, or whatever you want to say in the
chat.

00:00:52.569 --> 00:00:56.128
Don't let the chat distract you, because God
has a word for you today.

00:00:56.128 --> 00:00:57.838
Tell your neighbor, "Don't distract me today.

00:00:57.838 --> 00:01:03.058
God is going to speak to me today."

00:01:03.058 --> 00:01:07.609
Look at them and say, "You look so good you're
distracting me right now, but stop distracting

00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:16.319
me."

00:01:16.319 --> 00:01:18.728
God is going to speak to us today.

00:01:18.728 --> 00:01:25.468
Acts, chapter 3, verse 13.

00:01:25.468 --> 00:01:30.608
I really want to go to verse 19, so I will.

00:01:30.608 --> 00:01:35.759
I said that like it was something I really
wanted, but we can do it.

00:01:35.759 --> 00:01:40.138
Let's just do it.

00:01:40.138 --> 00:01:45.379
"The God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob…"

00:01:45.379 --> 00:01:46.379
Starting off strong.

00:01:46.379 --> 00:01:52.079
"…the God of our fathers, has glorified
his servant Jesus.

00:01:52.079 --> 00:01:56.599
You handed him over to be killed, and you
disowned him before Pilate, though he had

00:01:56.599 --> 00:01:58.729
decided to let him go.

00:01:58.729 --> 00:02:03.319
You disowned the Holy and Righteous One and
asked that a murderer be released to you.

00:02:03.319 --> 00:02:10.209
You killed the author of life, but God raised
him from the dead.

00:02:10.209 --> 00:02:12.339
We are witnesses of this.

00:02:12.339 --> 00:02:25.168
By faith in 
the name of Jesus, this man whom you see and

00:02:25.168 --> 00:02:27.278
know was made strong.

00:02:27.278 --> 00:02:33.339
It is Jesus' name and the faith that comes
through him that has completely healed him,

00:02:33.339 --> 00:02:35.189
as you can all see.

00:02:35.189 --> 00:02:42.058
Now, fellow Israelites, I know that you acted
in ignorance, as did your leaders.

00:02:42.058 --> 00:02:56.399
But this [what you did in ignorance] is how
God fulfilled what he had foretold through

00:02:56.399 --> 00:03:00.638
all the prophets, saying that his Messiah
would suffer.

00:03:00.638 --> 00:03:11.918
Repent, then, [change your mind, change your
direction,] and turn to God, so that your

00:03:11.918 --> 00:03:18.189
sins may be wiped out, that times of refreshing
may come from the Lord…"

00:03:18.189 --> 00:03:20.528
Go back to verse 15.

00:03:20.528 --> 00:03:23.179
It's the nucleus of this message.

00:03:23.179 --> 00:03:28.379
"You killed the author of life, but God raised
him from the dead.

00:03:28.379 --> 00:03:31.669
We are witnesses of this."

00:03:31.669 --> 00:03:39.769
Today I want to talk to you about What Comes
After.

00:03:39.769 --> 00:03:41.979
That's what the Lord wants me to talk to you
about.

00:03:41.979 --> 00:03:45.829
You know how you've been stressing out about
stuff that's out there somewhere?

00:03:45.829 --> 00:03:49.009
The Lord said, "Let's talk about what comes
after."

00:03:49.009 --> 00:03:54.739
You know how you've been stuck in some things
that happened, and you keep tripping on stuff

00:03:54.739 --> 00:03:55.739
that's behind you?

00:03:55.739 --> 00:03:58.129
How do you even trip on something that's behind
you?

00:03:58.129 --> 00:04:04.579
But the Lord said, "Let's talk today for just
a few moments about what comes after."

00:04:04.579 --> 00:04:07.739
Thank you for your Word, God.

00:04:07.739 --> 00:04:11.439
In Jesus' name, amen.

00:04:11.439 --> 00:04:15.419
While you're getting situated, quick plug.

00:04:15.419 --> 00:04:18.589
Holly has a book club.

00:04:18.589 --> 00:04:20.189
You have two fans, babe.

00:04:20.189 --> 00:04:22.889
It sounds like you need a new marketing department.

00:04:22.889 --> 00:04:25.659
No, it's awesome.

00:04:25.659 --> 00:04:30.289
She has a book club, and it is called the
Holly Furtick Book Club.

00:04:30.289 --> 00:04:32.679
Very creative title.

00:04:32.679 --> 00:04:37.159
I love it, because when I asked her why she
was doing it, she said, "Because I want to."

00:04:37.159 --> 00:04:39.429
Nothing deep about it.

00:04:39.429 --> 00:04:44.219
They don't always study books about "Seven
Ways to Pray Your Way into a Greater Day."

00:04:44.219 --> 00:04:45.669
They just study books she likes.

00:04:45.669 --> 00:04:46.779
They don't really even study them.

00:04:46.779 --> 00:04:47.779
Why am I saying "study"?

00:04:47.779 --> 00:04:50.079
They just talk about them.

00:04:50.079 --> 00:04:52.579
It's cool because she'll often get the author
on.

00:04:52.579 --> 00:04:54.799
She's so excited when she gets the author.

00:04:54.799 --> 00:04:56.989
She'll call me into the room or come running
in.

00:04:56.989 --> 00:04:58.459
She'll be like, "I got the author!"

00:04:58.459 --> 00:05:00.829
I'm like, "That's great, babe."

00:05:00.829 --> 00:05:01.829
Then I pick on her.

00:05:01.829 --> 00:05:07.169
I'm like, "But, you know, I have a book club
too."

00:05:07.169 --> 00:05:12.029
She's always trying to get me to read the
books.

00:05:12.029 --> 00:05:13.209
I'm like, "No, babe.

00:05:13.209 --> 00:05:14.209
I'm sorry.

00:05:14.209 --> 00:05:21.169
I have a book club, and the Author lives in
my heart."

00:05:21.169 --> 00:05:23.219
You have to feel so sorry for my family.

00:05:23.219 --> 00:05:27.209
They get dad jokes and preacher jokes and
both of them combined.

00:05:27.209 --> 00:05:30.999
It's unbearable, let me tell you right now.

00:05:30.999 --> 00:05:32.839
But I joke with her.

00:05:32.839 --> 00:05:33.839
I don't know.

00:05:33.839 --> 00:05:35.089
It's probably not because I'm studying the
Bible.

00:05:35.089 --> 00:05:36.089
I'm probably just lazy.

00:05:36.089 --> 00:05:41.779
I always intend to read the books that she
does, and I never get around to it.

00:05:41.779 --> 00:05:45.689
So she'll usually take me to go see the movie,
if there is a movie, and I will do that.

00:05:45.689 --> 00:05:47.269
She took me to see one recently.

00:05:47.269 --> 00:05:50.619
I won't tell you what the movie is so it won't
be like a spoiler alert if you want to go

00:05:50.619 --> 00:05:51.619
see that movie.

00:05:51.619 --> 00:05:52.899
I hated it.

00:05:52.899 --> 00:05:53.949
I thought the movie was terrible.

00:05:53.949 --> 00:05:55.809
It was kind of a last-minute decision.

00:05:55.809 --> 00:06:00.909
We snuck some low-carb candy into the movie
theater, and I sat there and watched that

00:06:00.909 --> 00:06:02.119
movie.

00:06:02.119 --> 00:06:07.179
Within five minutes, she turns to me and goes,
"I'm so sorry."

00:06:07.179 --> 00:06:08.799
Then you know what she's going to say next.

00:06:08.799 --> 00:06:11.279
"I promise the book was so much better."

00:06:11.279 --> 00:06:18.449
About every five minutes, she would turn to
me and say, "I promise the book was better."

00:06:18.449 --> 00:06:21.269
I didn't read the book, so I'm like, "Yeah,
right.

00:06:21.269 --> 00:06:24.109
How would I know if you're telling me the
truth?"

00:06:24.109 --> 00:06:28.959
One day I'm going to preach a Scripture that
says, "You are living epistles" and talk about

00:06:28.959 --> 00:06:34.209
how God wants to put his Word through our
lives living, and then I'm going to ask, "Was

00:06:34.209 --> 00:06:36.609
the book better?

00:06:36.609 --> 00:06:38.199
Are you living out…?"

00:06:38.199 --> 00:06:41.679
So, I'm going to do that one day.

00:06:41.679 --> 00:06:44.389
She said, "I promise the book was better."

00:06:44.389 --> 00:06:52.879
After two hours of me thinking, "I really
love you to sit through this movie…"

00:06:52.879 --> 00:06:56.989
I didn't like it at all.

00:06:56.989 --> 00:07:01.259
It did something I didn't expect it to do.

00:07:01.259 --> 00:07:07.199
The last scene of the movie, I was literally
getting my keys, getting my wallet, literally

00:07:07.199 --> 00:07:08.369
thinking, "Let's just go ahead and go.

00:07:08.369 --> 00:07:10.869
I don't need this long last scene."

00:07:10.869 --> 00:07:13.339
What happened in the last two minutes…

00:07:13.339 --> 00:07:24.729
I looked at her and said, "That was a pretty
good movie.

00:07:24.729 --> 00:07:31.129
I did not see that coming."

00:07:31.129 --> 00:07:38.939
The last two minutes changed the whole movie,
from me wanting a refund to me wanting to

00:07:38.939 --> 00:07:39.939
rewatch it.

00:07:39.939 --> 00:07:43.239
I'm like, "Maybe we should come back and see
that again, because I need to watch everything

00:07:43.239 --> 00:07:54.529
that I thought was stupid and slow and corny
through the lens of the last thing that happened."

00:07:54.529 --> 00:08:02.859
What I saw in the last two minutes made me
rethink the whole last two hours because of

00:08:02.859 --> 00:08:08.589
what I saw at the end that I didn't know in
the beginning, and I didn't know in the middle,

00:08:08.589 --> 00:08:13.549
but then when I saw the end, it changed the
middle, it changed the beginning, and it made

00:08:13.549 --> 00:08:18.659
me think, "Maybe you are a good book picker.

00:08:18.659 --> 00:08:20.949
Maybe this movie wasn't so bad after all."

00:08:20.949 --> 00:08:29.219
In life, wouldn't it be nice if we could see
the last two minutes, the last two months,

00:08:29.219 --> 00:08:38.909
the last two years, just to know how to watch
everything that is happening in real time?

00:08:38.909 --> 00:08:45.279
Something can happen at the end that makes
you go back and rethink the entire thing that

00:08:45.279 --> 00:08:46.359
went before it.

00:08:46.359 --> 00:08:47.819
You know I'm right.

00:08:47.819 --> 00:08:52.299
You can have experiences in life that make
you go from "Thank you, Lord, for bringing

00:08:52.299 --> 00:08:57.469
this person into my life, for this relationship,"
to "Lord, why didn't you protect me from this

00:08:57.469 --> 00:08:58.579
relationship?

00:08:58.579 --> 00:09:01.319
Why didn't I listen to all of the people who
told me…?"

00:09:01.319 --> 00:09:02.319
You know I'm right.

00:09:02.319 --> 00:09:04.389
There are things that can happen later.

00:09:04.389 --> 00:09:05.389
Here's what it is.

00:09:05.389 --> 00:09:06.949
I was thinking.

00:09:06.949 --> 00:09:11.219
Did the last two minutes change the first
two hours?

00:09:11.219 --> 00:09:12.719
Can you change the past?

00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:21.169
Before you say, "No," reconsider my illustration
in light of this book club we've chosen to

00:09:21.169 --> 00:09:22.169
attend today.

00:09:22.169 --> 00:09:24.019
We're in a book club.

00:09:24.019 --> 00:09:25.019
Right?

00:09:25.019 --> 00:09:32.669
We read something that happened not at the
beginning of the ministry of Peter and John

00:09:32.669 --> 00:09:35.519
and not at the end.

00:09:35.519 --> 00:09:40.239
We read something that happened right there
in the middle that was so powerful, this miracle

00:09:40.239 --> 00:09:41.239
that was so powerful.

00:09:41.239 --> 00:09:42.559
I love it.

00:09:42.559 --> 00:09:44.429
I've been studying this all week.

00:09:44.429 --> 00:09:49.820
I know what comes before, I know what comes
after, and right in the middle of it, Peter

00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:50.939
is preaching.

00:09:50.939 --> 00:09:53.059
He says something, and there's a word from
God.

00:09:53.059 --> 00:09:54.799
Actually, there are two words from God.

00:09:54.799 --> 00:10:00.639
Usually I get up to give you a word from God,
but you picked "Double Portion Sunday" today.

00:10:00.639 --> 00:10:04.189
There are two words from God in this text.

00:10:04.189 --> 00:10:09.349
Now, before we get there, let's back out one
more time and consider the premise.

00:10:09.349 --> 00:10:11.529
Can you change the past?

00:10:11.529 --> 00:10:15.709
Certainly, we can't redo the events.

00:10:15.709 --> 00:10:17.719
That's a waste of time.

00:10:17.719 --> 00:10:22.819
I think all regret is a misappropriation of
imagination.

00:10:22.819 --> 00:10:28.789
It's you taking the wisdom God wants you to
use for your future and applying it toward

00:10:28.789 --> 00:10:33.029
a situation that is already behind you.

00:10:33.029 --> 00:10:36.619
So, can you change the past?

00:10:36.619 --> 00:10:40.359
Apparently, Peter thinks you can.

00:10:40.359 --> 00:10:41.879
Not change the events.

00:10:41.879 --> 00:10:50.459
By the way, we're always changing the past
when we tell somebody else what happened.

00:10:50.459 --> 00:10:57.969
You are the senior editor of your story, and
you make all kinds of changes and alterations.

00:10:57.969 --> 00:10:59.879
You switch stuff around.

00:10:59.879 --> 00:11:02.929
You add dialogue…internal dialogue, external
dialogue.

00:11:02.929 --> 00:11:08.369
You are an unreliable narrator, to put it
in book terms, because this is a book club.

00:11:08.369 --> 00:11:09.369
Right?

00:11:09.369 --> 00:11:12.439
Now, the Bible is not a book like we say it's
a book.

00:11:12.439 --> 00:11:18.509
It has 62 separate books, different types
of literature, everything from poetry to historical

00:11:18.509 --> 00:11:22.889
narrative to letters that were written to
the church to instruct them how to live.

00:11:22.889 --> 00:11:29.769
Then you have the Gospels, which give the
record of the account of what Jesus did while

00:11:29.769 --> 00:11:31.459
he was here.

00:11:31.459 --> 00:11:39.039
The book of Acts is awesome because it tells
us what happened after Jesus left.

00:11:39.039 --> 00:11:45.059
Now we know that this movement that was beginning
here in Acts, chapter 3, is something that

00:11:45.059 --> 00:11:52.439
will still occupy a space in time in 2022
(2023 if you watch it later or 2025 if you

00:11:52.439 --> 00:11:53.779
watch it later).

00:11:53.779 --> 00:11:55.599
God knows all of that.

00:11:55.599 --> 00:11:58.499
God knows when you're going to watch this
message.

00:11:58.499 --> 00:12:02.949
What Peter didn't know is that I was going
to be bringing his words that he had to say

00:12:02.949 --> 00:12:10.049
on the spot to you today for your situation
and that you would be in a situation today

00:12:10.049 --> 00:12:15.559
where you don't know what's next and you can't
figure out what's happening.

00:12:15.559 --> 00:12:19.319
The challenge of it is we don't get to see
the last scene.

00:12:19.319 --> 00:12:22.799
The disciples didn't get to see the last scene.

00:12:22.799 --> 00:12:28.449
They didn't get to see that this would work,
that the gospel would indeed go from Jerusalem

00:12:28.449 --> 00:12:34.489
(that's where they started) to Judea (the
surrounding area) to Samaria (where they tended

00:12:34.489 --> 00:12:43.309
to avoid) and to the ends of the earth (Ballantyne,
Gaston, Riverwalk, Columbia).

00:12:43.309 --> 00:12:45.709
The ends of the earth…Kentucky.

00:12:45.709 --> 00:12:49.129
Peter didn't know about Kentucky when he preached
this, but I guarantee there's somebody right

00:12:49.129 --> 00:12:50.369
now who's watching us from Kentucky.

00:12:50.369 --> 00:12:52.999
They weren't paying attention, and all of
a sudden, I just got their attention because

00:12:52.999 --> 00:12:53.999
I said "Kentucky."

00:12:53.999 --> 00:12:56.089
Yeah, the Lord wanted me to say, "Kentucky,"
because he knew you'd need this word right

00:12:56.089 --> 00:12:57.089
now.

00:12:57.089 --> 00:13:01.609
God is like that.

00:13:01.609 --> 00:13:10.019
My challenge is…How do I live through this
story when I don't know the last scene that

00:13:10.019 --> 00:13:13.559
may make it all make sense?

00:13:13.559 --> 00:13:27.269
That's why I have to live 

00:13:27.269 --> 00:13:28.319
by faith.

00:13:28.319 --> 00:13:29.359
By faith.

00:13:29.359 --> 00:13:33.629
We walk by faith, not by sight.

00:13:33.629 --> 00:13:37.259
So, it means that even though I haven't seen
the last scene…

00:13:37.259 --> 00:13:39.019
"Is my kid going to come back home?"

00:13:39.019 --> 00:13:40.999
I haven't seen the last scene.

00:13:40.999 --> 00:13:42.339
"Is my marriage going to make it?"

00:13:42.339 --> 00:13:44.419
I haven't seen the last scene.

00:13:44.419 --> 00:13:46.129
"Am I ever going to get through this?"

00:13:46.129 --> 00:13:48.069
I haven't seen the last scene.

00:13:48.069 --> 00:13:51.069
"Am I going to get another job while I keep
getting all of these other bills?

00:13:51.069 --> 00:13:53.169
I keep getting other bills, but I haven't
got another job.

00:13:53.169 --> 00:13:56.779
If I get the other job, am I going to make
enough in the other job to pay all of the

00:13:56.779 --> 00:13:59.339
other bills, because all of the other bills
didn't stop coming while I was waiting on

00:13:59.339 --> 00:14:00.339
the other job?"

00:14:00.339 --> 00:14:09.069
Even though I haven't seen that scene, by
faith I can believe that if God said he was

00:14:09.069 --> 00:14:14.829
with me…

00:14:14.829 --> 00:14:17.499
He knows what's next, and I can trust him.

00:14:17.499 --> 00:14:18.499
Selah.

00:14:18.499 --> 00:14:20.678
Pause and think about it.

00:14:20.678 --> 00:14:26.339
In this scene of your life, you can believe
that what God is working in your life, in

00:14:26.339 --> 00:14:33.189
your family, in your career, in my ministry,
in my heart, in my character…

00:14:33.189 --> 00:14:41.189
Even though I don't get to see the last scene,
I can turn to Holly and say, "This is going

00:14:41.189 --> 00:14:54.699
to be good," because I trust who wrote the
screenplay.

00:14:54.699 --> 00:14:58.279
Peter is coming on kind of strong in this
sermon, you have to admit, but he's fired

00:14:58.279 --> 00:14:59.569
up.

00:14:59.569 --> 00:15:00.799
You know how you get fired up?

00:15:00.799 --> 00:15:02.189
You get on a spiritual high.

00:15:02.189 --> 00:15:04.779
Have you ever been on a spiritual high?

00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:05.779
No?

00:15:05.779 --> 00:15:11.319
Certainly, it's a lot different than what
you just demonstrated.

00:15:11.319 --> 00:15:14.408
Maybe today is not the day.

00:15:14.408 --> 00:15:19.019
Peter had done something pretty amazing.

00:15:19.019 --> 00:15:23.559
Jesus used to help them do miracles, but now
he's no longer here in human form, and he

00:15:23.559 --> 00:15:24.559
sent his Spirit.

00:15:24.559 --> 00:15:28.798
He was always telling them while he walked
the earth, "I'm going to leave, but after

00:15:28.798 --> 00:15:34.798
I do, I'll send something that will give you
a power I can't give you while I'm here, so

00:15:34.798 --> 00:15:36.339
wait for that.

00:15:36.339 --> 00:15:37.609
Don't get discouraged.

00:15:37.609 --> 00:15:38.819
I'm going to die.

00:15:38.819 --> 00:15:43.009
I'll be there three days, but don't give up
in three days.

00:15:43.009 --> 00:15:47.039
Don't give up in 10 days, 20 days, 30 days,
or 50 days.

00:15:47.039 --> 00:15:51.419
When they're persecuting you, know that they
persecuted me.

00:15:51.419 --> 00:15:55.309
I'm giving you a spirit, the Spirit of God."

00:15:55.309 --> 00:15:59.169
On the day of Pentecost, the Spirit came.

00:15:59.169 --> 00:16:03.159
They were all together in one place, and the
Spirit came.

00:16:03.159 --> 00:16:06.979
That's where your strength comes from: the
Spirit of God.

00:16:06.979 --> 00:16:08.569
It doesn't come from you.

00:16:08.569 --> 00:16:10.119
It doesn't come from situations.

00:16:10.119 --> 00:16:12.149
It doesn't come from earthly things.

00:16:12.149 --> 00:16:14.249
It doesn't come from creatine.

00:16:14.249 --> 00:16:21.069
I have some strength that comes from Jesus
Christ who sent the Spirit in his name from

00:16:21.069 --> 00:16:23.919
the Father and lives forever to make intercession.

00:16:23.919 --> 00:16:27.649
I have his Spirit, see.

00:16:27.649 --> 00:16:29.259
So this is Peter.

00:16:29.259 --> 00:16:30.259
Watch.

00:16:30.259 --> 00:16:31.978
I divide Peter's life into two separate things.

00:16:31.978 --> 00:16:41.218
I call him "Before Spirit Peter," or "BS Peter,"
and then "After Spirit Peter."

00:16:41.218 --> 00:16:43.919
This is AS Peter, not BS Peter.

00:16:43.919 --> 00:16:48.299
BS Peter, before the Spirit came in him, was
saying all kinds of stuff he couldn't back

00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:49.299
up.

00:16:49.299 --> 00:16:50.299
"I've got you, Jesus.

00:16:50.299 --> 00:16:51.299
I don't care about anything.

00:16:51.299 --> 00:16:52.299
Give me that sword!

00:16:52.299 --> 00:16:53.299
Give me that ear!"

00:16:53.299 --> 00:16:58.860
He was doing Mr. Potato Head preaching before
he got filled with the Spirit.

00:16:58.860 --> 00:17:01.619
Now Jesus is gone, but the Spirit came, and
he's bold.

00:17:01.619 --> 00:17:02.759
This must be a different dude.

00:17:02.759 --> 00:17:06.369
This can't be the same dude who sat down at
the fire and, when a little servant girl asked,

00:17:06.369 --> 00:17:10.389
"Were you one of them?" said, "I don't know
him" and started cussing.

00:17:10.389 --> 00:17:11.779
Now he's preaching.

00:17:11.779 --> 00:17:13.029
That's who spoke these words.

00:17:13.029 --> 00:17:14.869
I didn't tell you that.

00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:18.729
I wanted to save it, because I wanted you
to see the words, and then I wanted you to

00:17:18.729 --> 00:17:24.078
think about who said them and when he said
them and why he said them.

00:17:24.078 --> 00:17:25.078
Look at it again.

00:17:25.078 --> 00:17:26.169
He goes all the way back.

00:17:26.169 --> 00:17:29.359
"The God of Abraham…"

00:17:29.359 --> 00:17:36.419
He hits rewind all the way back to the beginning
of the book, to the beginning of the movie,

00:17:36.419 --> 00:17:42.279
because something happened in this moment
that made him rethink the whole thing.

00:17:42.279 --> 00:17:43.639
He's speaking to the Jewish people.

00:17:43.639 --> 00:17:50.749
They're familiar with this God, but as he
rewinds to that first frame and says, "The

00:17:50.749 --> 00:17:58.549
God of Abraham," he reminds you and me that
it starts with God.

00:17:58.549 --> 00:18:09.379
It didn't start when your mom and dad decided
it was time to try and succeeded.

00:18:09.379 --> 00:18:14.689
It didn't start when the fastest swimmer made
it all the way.

00:18:14.689 --> 00:18:16.959
(Just waking y'all up.)

00:18:16.959 --> 00:18:20.259
It didn't start with any of that.

00:18:20.259 --> 00:18:22.639
It starts with God.

00:18:22.639 --> 00:18:25.559
Everybody is running, because here's what
happened.

00:18:25.559 --> 00:18:27.639
I cannot preach this whole text.

00:18:27.639 --> 00:18:29.019
Just read it this week.

00:18:29.019 --> 00:18:31.579
Just promise me you'll try to read it this
week.

00:18:31.579 --> 00:18:34.249
They're going to the temple at the hour of
prayer.

00:18:34.249 --> 00:18:35.479
There are three times of prayer.

00:18:35.479 --> 00:18:38.239
They're at this particular time of prayer.

00:18:38.239 --> 00:18:40.879
The word hour literally means a divine appointment.

00:18:40.879 --> 00:18:41.879
They didn't know that.

00:18:41.879 --> 00:18:43.239
They're going to the temple.

00:18:43.239 --> 00:18:48.249
This man is at the gate, and he can't walk,
and he asks for money.

00:18:48.249 --> 00:18:54.379
Peter is like, "I don't have what you asked
for, but I have what you need that you wouldn't

00:18:54.379 --> 00:18:59.639
even know to ask for because it's a name.

00:18:59.639 --> 00:19:04.489
Silver and gold have I none, but such as I
have I give you."

00:19:04.489 --> 00:19:06.069
This is what Peter said to the man.

00:19:06.069 --> 00:19:11.229
"In the name of Jesus, get up and walk."

00:19:11.229 --> 00:19:12.899
He reaches down.

00:19:12.899 --> 00:19:14.828
His hand becomes a jumper cable.

00:19:14.828 --> 00:19:16.929
The man jumps up to his feet.

00:19:16.929 --> 00:19:19.979
He starts going to church, but not like everybody
else.

00:19:19.979 --> 00:19:22.009
He's high-stepping to church.

00:19:22.009 --> 00:19:25.639
He's walking, jumping, praising God.

00:19:25.639 --> 00:19:29.849
How many of y'all came in this morning jumping
and praising God?

00:19:29.849 --> 00:19:32.399
You know you're lying.

00:19:32.399 --> 00:19:37.799
You came in dragging and fighting and cussing
and fussing, and then when you saw the greeters,

00:19:37.799 --> 00:19:39.679
you said, "Praise the Lord."

00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:40.969
"How are you?"

00:19:40.969 --> 00:19:42.499
"I'm blessed and highly favored."

00:19:42.499 --> 00:19:48.519
Anyway, there's so much we could say about
this miracle.

00:19:48.519 --> 00:19:53.119
He didn't leave the way he came, and all of
that.

00:19:53.119 --> 00:19:57.119
Today I want to do what Peter did, and I want
to go back.

00:19:57.119 --> 00:20:01.999
This man gets healed, and all of the people
don't know what to think about it, so Peter

00:20:01.999 --> 00:20:02.999
takes the opportunity.

00:20:02.999 --> 00:20:07.159
You know, a lot of times, God does something
in our lives on a physical level, but we don't

00:20:07.159 --> 00:20:11.289
stop to reflect on it and break it down on
a spiritual level, so we don't get the full

00:20:11.289 --> 00:20:14.439
benefit of what he did.

00:20:14.439 --> 00:20:20.009
Peter sees this man who gets healed, and he
sees, "This would make an excellent opportunity

00:20:20.009 --> 00:20:21.899
to preach."

00:20:21.899 --> 00:20:29.939
There's a man whose name is not known or mentioned
who is healed by a name that is above every

00:20:29.939 --> 00:20:37.319
name, and the vessel for it is a man who really
was an unlikely candidate.

00:20:37.319 --> 00:20:44.119
I would call the book of Acts, if I gave it
a subtitle, "The Unfolding Plan of an Unstoppable

00:20:44.119 --> 00:20:46.619
God Through Unlikely People."

00:20:46.619 --> 00:20:48.509
Like Peter.

00:20:48.509 --> 00:20:50.408
Like me.

00:20:50.408 --> 00:20:51.779
Like you.

00:20:51.779 --> 00:20:53.169
The unfolding plan.

00:20:53.169 --> 00:20:54.939
They didn't know it when they were in it.

00:20:54.939 --> 00:20:56.578
You don't know it when you're in it.

00:20:56.578 --> 00:20:58.489
You can't see it when you're in it.

00:20:58.489 --> 00:21:02.799
You'll be grabbing your keys and grabbing
your wallet and getting up to leave and starting

00:21:02.799 --> 00:21:07.059
to give up and thinking about quitting and
thinking about walking away and turning to

00:21:07.059 --> 00:21:09.319
the person next to you and saying, "This is
ridiculous.

00:21:09.319 --> 00:21:10.448
I wasted my money.

00:21:10.448 --> 00:21:11.619
I wasted my time.

00:21:11.619 --> 00:21:12.719
I wasted my prayers.

00:21:12.719 --> 00:21:13.819
I wasted my faith.

00:21:13.819 --> 00:21:15.198
I'm wasting my life.

00:21:15.198 --> 00:21:16.399
What was it all for?

00:21:16.399 --> 00:21:18.229
It keeps hurting, and it won't go away.

00:21:18.229 --> 00:21:20.069
I keep trying, and I can't get up."

00:21:20.069 --> 00:21:31.779
But in this moment, Peter is taking the opportunity
to remind you of Jesus who is, Hebrews 12:2

00:21:31.779 --> 00:21:38.969
says, the author and the finisher of our faith.

00:21:38.969 --> 00:21:40.979
So, here's the challenge.

00:21:40.979 --> 00:21:50.989
Philip Yancey said faith is believing in advance
what will only make sense in reverse.

00:21:50.989 --> 00:21:56.339
Faith for what you can't figure out; faith
for what frustrates you; faith for what has

00:21:56.339 --> 00:22:01.439
you tied up in knots; faith for what wakes
you up in the middle of the night; faith for

00:22:01.439 --> 00:22:05.809
what makes you think you're losing your mind;
faith for what makes you wonder, "Am I going

00:22:05.809 --> 00:22:09.869
crazy?"; faith for what you've given up on
the possibility of change for.

00:22:09.869 --> 00:22:12.398
That kind of faith, he says…

00:22:12.398 --> 00:22:15.119
We have to go all the way back.

00:22:15.119 --> 00:22:16.149
Watch this.

00:22:16.149 --> 00:22:22.369
This man has just been healed, and Peter starts
talking about history.

00:22:22.369 --> 00:22:28.749
What does this man's healing have to do with
the Jewish people's history?

00:22:28.749 --> 00:22:32.849
What does healing have to do with history?

00:22:32.849 --> 00:22:34.259
Everything.

00:22:34.259 --> 00:22:38.489
Do you understand?

00:22:38.489 --> 00:22:46.059
If you are in the history only, then you won't
experience your destiny, but if you are only

00:22:46.059 --> 00:22:53.519
focused on your destiny and have no frame
of your history, you will give up too soon

00:22:53.519 --> 00:22:59.828
and miss the point of what God is doing in
your life.

00:22:59.828 --> 00:23:01.769
The God of Abraham.

00:23:01.769 --> 00:23:03.389
We're going all the way back to Abraham, Peter?

00:23:03.389 --> 00:23:04.939
Peter is like, "Yeah.

00:23:04.939 --> 00:23:06.639
I'm going all the way back."

00:23:06.639 --> 00:23:10.639
This is like when you ask somebody how they're
doing, and they're like, "When I was 3…"

00:23:10.639 --> 00:23:13.069
You're like, "Whoa.

00:23:13.069 --> 00:23:15.698
How are you doing right now?"

00:23:15.698 --> 00:23:18.859
All they want to see is "Is this real?

00:23:18.859 --> 00:23:20.179
Did that man…?"

00:23:20.179 --> 00:23:21.219
Let's give him a name.

00:23:21.219 --> 00:23:22.698
"That's Rob.

00:23:22.698 --> 00:23:26.448
Rob is not supposed to be walking."

00:23:26.448 --> 00:23:27.448
Let's call him Jimmy.

00:23:27.448 --> 00:23:29.828
"Jimmy is not supposed to be jumping.

00:23:29.828 --> 00:23:31.439
Is Jimmy jumping?

00:23:31.439 --> 00:23:32.959
I heard Jimmy was out here jumping.

00:23:32.959 --> 00:23:33.969
Jimmy can't be jumping.

00:23:33.969 --> 00:23:35.189
We walked right over him."

00:23:35.189 --> 00:23:36.749
Now, this is something awesome.

00:23:36.749 --> 00:23:38.159
God can shift things so quickly.

00:23:38.159 --> 00:23:43.959
The one everybody stepped over is now the
center of the story.

00:23:43.959 --> 00:23:45.599
God can shift it like that.

00:23:45.599 --> 00:23:50.599
So, don't worry when people say something
about you or don't worry when people don't

00:23:50.599 --> 00:23:54.559
give you an opportunity or don't worry when
they don't text you back.

00:23:54.559 --> 00:24:04.489
You needed that space on your phone for what's
coming after.

00:24:04.489 --> 00:24:10.318
I love the Word of God.

00:24:10.318 --> 00:24:13.809
The man is healed, and Peter is like, "The
God of Abraham…"

00:24:13.809 --> 00:24:17.818
Because it starts with God.

00:24:17.818 --> 00:24:19.698
Look.

00:24:19.698 --> 00:24:24.119
Your story, whatever scene you're in right
now…divorce, heartbreak, victory, success,

00:24:24.119 --> 00:24:27.059
promotion, termination…any of it…

00:24:27.059 --> 00:24:38.799
Your story is a story in a story in a story
in a story in a story.

00:24:38.799 --> 00:24:43.019
I should do this 41 times…in a story, in
a story.

00:24:43.019 --> 00:24:44.639
Put it in the chat: "In a story."

00:24:44.639 --> 00:24:49.499
Say it out loud: "In a story."

00:24:49.499 --> 00:24:53.549
That's how many generations back Peter goes
to explain what happened.

00:24:53.549 --> 00:24:55.219
"The God of Abraham…"

00:24:55.219 --> 00:24:58.229
That's 41 generations before Jesus.

00:24:58.229 --> 00:25:01.339
"Peter, can you kind of tell us what's just
going on right now?

00:25:01.339 --> 00:25:03.458
Give me the CliffsNotes, Peter.

00:25:03.458 --> 00:25:05.229
I'm not sure I want a whole history lesson."

00:25:05.229 --> 00:25:06.229
No, no, no.

00:25:06.229 --> 00:25:19.839
You have to understand history or you'll look
at this man and think it's his story.

00:25:19.839 --> 00:25:27.769
Peter has to show him it's not just his story,
and it's not just your story.

00:25:27.769 --> 00:25:37.489
It's his story, the God of Abraham.

00:25:37.489 --> 00:25:41.309
I'm living in the middle of his story.

00:25:41.309 --> 00:25:42.309
That encourages me.

00:25:42.309 --> 00:25:43.309
I don't know why.

00:25:43.309 --> 00:25:46.819
When it's all my story, it's all my drama.

00:25:46.819 --> 00:25:49.759
When it's all my story, it's all on my budget.

00:25:49.759 --> 00:25:52.889
If he's the director, he has to pay the bills.

00:25:52.889 --> 00:25:56.179
If he's the director, he has to figure out
the script.

00:25:56.179 --> 00:26:02.469
If it's his story, he has to figure out how
to make all this chaos and all this crazy

00:26:02.469 --> 00:26:07.869
and all of these world events and all of these
hurts and all of these mistakes work together

00:26:07.869 --> 00:26:15.899
to serve the purpose of the Author who created
me from my mother's womb.

00:26:15.899 --> 00:26:25.549
So, stepping right into the middle of his
story, this man at the gate, Peter recalls

00:26:25.549 --> 00:26:26.799
his story.

00:26:26.799 --> 00:26:31.759
It's a story within a story within a story.

00:26:31.759 --> 00:26:36.379
You hang around here long enough, I'm going
to teach you the Bible.

00:26:36.379 --> 00:26:37.899
Abraham is 75.

00:26:37.899 --> 00:26:41.919
His story is coming to a close at 75.

00:26:41.919 --> 00:26:43.739
Right?

00:26:43.739 --> 00:26:48.688
You haven't talked to the Author yet, Abraham.

00:26:48.688 --> 00:26:50.479
The Author showed up to Abraham.

00:26:50.479 --> 00:26:52.399
He didn't even have an H in his name.

00:26:52.399 --> 00:26:56.559
Vanna didn't even put an H in his name yet.

00:26:56.559 --> 00:26:58.939
I watch Wheel of Fortune every Wednesday night
with my mom.

00:26:58.939 --> 00:27:02.619
I'm wild and crazy every Wednesday night.

00:27:02.619 --> 00:27:08.539
It's called "Wednesdays for the Wheel," and
I pray for Pat Sajak every Wednesday.

00:27:08.539 --> 00:27:11.899
Pat, if you ever watch this, I would love
to have you at Elevation.

00:27:11.899 --> 00:27:12.989
I think you're amazing.

00:27:12.989 --> 00:27:16.328
(I'm just putting it out there in case God
wants to answer a dumb prayer.)

00:27:16.328 --> 00:27:23.159
"Abram, start counting stars."

00:27:23.159 --> 00:27:24.639
This is what the Author told him.

00:27:24.639 --> 00:27:26.669
"Start counting the stars, Lord?

00:27:26.669 --> 00:27:28.279
Yeah, you did good on those stars.

00:27:28.279 --> 00:27:29.279
That's cool, man."

00:27:29.279 --> 00:27:32.409
He's in Ur of the Chaldeans, and God says,
"Go to the land I will show you and count

00:27:32.409 --> 00:27:35.599
the stars, and if you can count them, that's
how numerous your descendants are going to

00:27:35.599 --> 00:27:36.599
be."

00:27:36.599 --> 00:27:37.689
That's what comes after.

00:27:37.689 --> 00:27:42.929
"Count the sand of the seashore."

00:27:42.929 --> 00:27:46.749
This is a collision of history and destiny,
because there's what God did (the stars) long

00:27:46.749 --> 00:27:52.429
before Abram got here, and there's what God
is doing through Abram.

00:27:52.429 --> 00:27:54.129
History…destiny.

00:27:54.129 --> 00:27:59.479
If you stay stuck in one and don't focus on
the other, you're done.

00:27:59.479 --> 00:28:01.739
If you stay just focused on the history…

00:28:01.739 --> 00:28:04.809
You're walking around talking about how much
you bench pressed in 1947.

00:28:04.809 --> 00:28:07.839
"I was the man back then, y'all.

00:28:07.839 --> 00:28:09.509
I see these kids these days.

00:28:09.509 --> 00:28:12.049
They don't know how we used to do it back
in the day."

00:28:12.049 --> 00:28:15.429
Now you're stuck in your history.

00:28:15.429 --> 00:28:18.519
You start talking about what you're going
to do one day when nobody is bothering you

00:28:18.519 --> 00:28:22.269
and there's no traffic and they make flying
Teslas and you don't have to wait to get to

00:28:22.269 --> 00:28:23.269
work.

00:28:23.269 --> 00:28:29.029
Well, that's just you hypothetically avoiding
this present moment.

00:28:29.029 --> 00:28:30.729
Wow!

00:28:30.729 --> 00:28:39.529
Thank you, God, that I'm not stuck where I
started.

00:28:39.529 --> 00:28:48.759
Lord, I thank you for that Scripture that
says, "No eye has seen, no ear has heard,

00:28:48.759 --> 00:28:53.509
neither has it entered into the heart of a
man what God has prepared for those who love

00:28:53.509 --> 00:28:55.659
him.

00:28:55.659 --> 00:29:02.149
But God has revealed them to us by his Spirit."

00:29:02.149 --> 00:29:03.479
Nobody ever says the next verse.

00:29:03.479 --> 00:29:05.389
I always heard the first verse.

00:29:05.389 --> 00:29:14.389
"No eye has seen, and no ear has heard what
has entered into the hearts of men."

00:29:14.389 --> 00:29:18.319
The next verse says, "But God…"

00:29:18.319 --> 00:29:24.759
Abraham was 75 years old, and his wife's womb
was as good as dead, but God wanted a baby

00:29:24.759 --> 00:29:26.429
named Isaac.

00:29:26.429 --> 00:29:32.259
Abraham even got in the way and messed it
up by having Ishmael with Hagar, but God had

00:29:32.259 --> 00:29:35.009
a plan for Isaac and Ishmael.

00:29:35.009 --> 00:29:36.119
But God.

00:29:36.119 --> 00:29:39.859
"But God has revealed them by his Spirit."

00:29:39.859 --> 00:29:40.869
That's what his Spirit does.

00:29:40.869 --> 00:29:42.879
That's what time with God does.

00:29:42.879 --> 00:29:46.839
That's why coming to church is a better investment
than the stock market.

00:29:46.839 --> 00:29:51.649
That's why coming to church is a better investment
than washing your raggedy car, which is going

00:29:51.649 --> 00:29:54.269
to be dirty again in three days.

00:29:54.269 --> 00:29:57.399
That's why coming to church and listening
to the Word of God…

00:29:57.399 --> 00:30:01.889
Because that Word gets in you, and when it
mixes with the Spirit that was in you, and

00:30:01.889 --> 00:30:07.509
the soil of the Spirit and the seed of the
Word get together…

00:30:07.509 --> 00:30:12.819
God said, "So shall your seed be."

00:30:12.819 --> 00:30:17.339
At the same time he's speaking to old Abe…

00:30:17.339 --> 00:30:20.318
"Are you sure about that?"

00:30:20.318 --> 00:30:25.269
The Lord is like, "I'm sure about that, because
I'm the Author."

00:30:25.269 --> 00:30:29.679
Holly got one author on the phone one time
on the Instagram, on her book club…

00:30:29.679 --> 00:30:30.679
Hollyfurtick.com.

00:30:30.679 --> 00:30:32.279
You can look it up.

00:30:32.279 --> 00:30:33.719
She told me to plug the website.

00:30:33.719 --> 00:30:36.469
I forgot to do that, so I'm going to do that.

00:30:36.469 --> 00:30:39.749
Maybe she'll pay me back in a sponsorship.

00:30:39.749 --> 00:30:41.289
You can sponsor me when we get home.

00:30:41.289 --> 00:30:42.289
All right?

00:30:42.289 --> 00:30:43.708
This will be a sponsored ad.

00:30:43.708 --> 00:30:45.909
Y'all quit looking at me.

00:30:45.909 --> 00:30:46.969
I'm uncomfortable.

00:30:46.969 --> 00:30:49.629
I shouldn't have said it.

00:30:49.629 --> 00:30:50.629
What comes after.

00:30:50.629 --> 00:30:51.818
That's a whole other sermon.

00:30:51.818 --> 00:30:53.599
That's a marriage seminar.

00:30:53.599 --> 00:30:55.438
Yeah, do the dishes.

00:30:55.438 --> 00:30:56.609
You might get a kiss.

00:30:56.609 --> 00:30:57.609
All right.

00:30:57.609 --> 00:30:59.139
What comes after.

00:30:59.139 --> 00:31:02.799
She was interviewing this author who wrote
a true story about her life.

00:31:02.799 --> 00:31:05.739
She gave up a baby for adoption, teenage pregnancy.

00:31:05.739 --> 00:31:11.109
When she got the author on the interview,
she said, "You left the story off right there

00:31:11.109 --> 00:31:13.659
at the end, and you never told us if you met
the kid."

00:31:13.659 --> 00:31:15.259
She goes, "Oh yeah.

00:31:15.259 --> 00:31:16.849
That's what my next book is about."

00:31:16.849 --> 00:31:19.078
Holly said, "Good.

00:31:19.078 --> 00:31:21.839
I can't wait to read it."

00:31:21.839 --> 00:31:29.229
Y'all, when we read the book of Acts, we're
reading the sequel.

00:31:29.229 --> 00:31:31.979
It was written by Luke, who was a doctor who
traveled with Paul.

00:31:31.979 --> 00:31:35.399
He wrote it while Paul was in prison in Rome.

00:31:35.399 --> 00:31:39.059
He wrote it to a man named Theophilus.

00:31:39.059 --> 00:31:41.688
He calls him "Most excellent Theophilus."

00:31:41.688 --> 00:31:46.039
I want y'all to start calling me that, by
the way: "Most excellent Pastor Steven."

00:31:46.039 --> 00:31:47.039
All right?

00:31:47.039 --> 00:31:49.349
Get on it.

00:31:49.349 --> 00:31:55.509
Twenty-six percent of the New Testament was
written by Luke to Theophilus.

00:31:55.509 --> 00:31:56.949
Who was Theophilus?

00:31:56.949 --> 00:32:00.189
I mean, Luke is writing to him.

00:32:00.189 --> 00:32:02.899
Luke isn't even one of the original twelve
disciples.

00:32:02.899 --> 00:32:04.759
He's a Gentile who came later.

00:32:04.759 --> 00:32:13.189
He writes his first book, self-titled debut
EP, Luke.

00:32:13.189 --> 00:32:19.849
Then he puts out the book of Acts as a follow-up,
the sequel.

00:32:19.849 --> 00:32:26.578
The disciples (I never saw it this way before)
are living in the sequel.

00:32:26.578 --> 00:32:28.808
Jesus is gone in bodily form.

00:32:28.808 --> 00:32:31.058
What they knew is no longer available.

00:32:31.058 --> 00:32:33.669
What was normal for them for three years has
been upended.

00:32:33.669 --> 00:32:35.299
The cross has happened.

00:32:35.299 --> 00:32:36.969
The resurrection has happened.

00:32:36.969 --> 00:32:38.578
The Spirit has come.

00:32:38.578 --> 00:32:41.879
There's persecution ahead, but there's progress
ahead.

00:32:41.879 --> 00:32:44.129
There is always persecution with progress.

00:32:44.129 --> 00:32:48.749
If it's not from the outside, it's going to
be from your lower nature and your flesh on

00:32:48.749 --> 00:32:49.749
the inside.

00:32:49.749 --> 00:32:52.948
There's always persecution with progress.

00:32:52.948 --> 00:32:56.469
I told y'all last week the Devil will step
right out of your way if you're headed in

00:32:56.469 --> 00:32:57.479
the wrong direction.

00:32:57.479 --> 00:32:58.829
Try it.

00:32:58.829 --> 00:32:59.829
Any football players in here?

00:32:59.829 --> 00:33:01.480
I heard there were basketball players in here
today.

00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:04.489
Is that right?

00:33:04.489 --> 00:33:05.709
All right.

00:33:05.709 --> 00:33:08.349
Do it when you get back when the season starts.

00:33:08.349 --> 00:33:13.779
Turn around and run toward the other goal
and see if anybody stops you.

00:33:13.779 --> 00:33:17.699
They'll let you do it all day long.

00:33:17.699 --> 00:33:19.149
They'll hand you a Gatorade.

00:33:19.149 --> 00:33:20.169
"Yeah, do that again."

00:33:20.169 --> 00:33:23.918
If you're putting points on the board for
the Devil, he'll assist you.

00:33:23.918 --> 00:33:26.479
He'll alley-oop you, but if you ever make
up your mind…

00:33:26.479 --> 00:33:27.479
"I'm following Jesus.

00:33:27.479 --> 00:33:28.479
No turning back.

00:33:28.479 --> 00:33:29.479
I'm going forward into the future.

00:33:29.479 --> 00:33:36.628
I have a father named Abraham who had a son
named Isaac who had a son named Jacob, and

00:33:36.628 --> 00:33:48.238
now his servant Jesus is being glorified."

00:33:48.238 --> 00:33:50.118
The unfolding plan.

00:33:50.118 --> 00:33:59.129
Corrie ten Boom said something like, "Heaven
has no panic, only plans."

00:33:59.129 --> 00:34:03.198
Think about what she went through, and she
still said that, not before it happened, but

00:34:03.198 --> 00:34:04.778
after.

00:34:04.778 --> 00:34:11.569
She's still standing there saying stuff like,
"Heaven has no panic, only plans."

00:34:11.569 --> 00:34:13.779
But it's an unfolding plan.

00:34:13.779 --> 00:34:14.988
You get the picture.

00:34:14.988 --> 00:34:16.309
You don't see the scene.

00:34:16.309 --> 00:34:28.679
So, by faith, I have to find out what God
can do, and I have to apply that to the area

00:34:28.679 --> 00:34:40.359
where I'm the most anxious right now and believe
by faith going forward based on the foundation

00:34:40.359 --> 00:34:48.118
of who God is, the God of Abraham, the God
of Isaac, the God of Jacob.

00:34:48.118 --> 00:34:50.678
Isaac was tied up on an altar.

00:34:50.678 --> 00:34:55.968
Just at the moment where he thought he was
going to be sacrificed, he heard a rustling

00:34:55.968 --> 00:35:00.748
of a ram in a bush, because God never intended
to kill Isaac.

00:35:00.748 --> 00:35:02.448
God always had a ram.

00:35:02.448 --> 00:35:09.529
The Bible says Jesus is the Lamb of God who
was slain from the foundation of the earth.

00:35:09.529 --> 00:35:11.099
When Peter stood at the cross…

00:35:11.099 --> 00:35:12.928
I have news for y'all.

00:35:12.928 --> 00:35:18.309
He didn't call it Good Friday.

00:35:18.309 --> 00:35:30.649
We call it that because we know what came
after.

00:35:30.649 --> 00:35:42.079
Question: What if it's good?

00:35:42.079 --> 00:35:51.498
We all know from broccoli that it can be good
and not taste good.

00:35:51.498 --> 00:35:53.388
We know that.

00:35:53.388 --> 00:35:54.388
What if it's good?

00:35:54.388 --> 00:36:00.208
Flip side: What if it's not?

00:36:00.208 --> 00:36:06.889
What if it makes you feel good, but it's not
good?

00:36:06.889 --> 00:36:11.368
I'm not calling anybody out or putting you
on the spot, but is there anybody watching

00:36:11.368 --> 00:36:14.559
online or at one of our campuses right now
who would raise your hand (if you want to

00:36:14.559 --> 00:36:18.279
raise your hand; you don't have to) who struggled
with addiction and went through recovery at

00:36:18.279 --> 00:36:20.948
some point in your life?

00:36:20.948 --> 00:36:22.459
Thank you for raising your hand.

00:36:22.459 --> 00:36:32.049
We're proud of you.

00:36:32.049 --> 00:36:36.948
You want to snatch people back now when you
see them going down that path, don't you?

00:36:36.948 --> 00:36:44.178
Because you know that after the high comes
the lowest low, and you know what it takes

00:36:44.178 --> 00:36:45.929
to break free from those chains.

00:36:45.929 --> 00:36:48.709
You know how hard it still is for you every
day.

00:36:48.709 --> 00:36:52.529
You just want to scream, like y'all want to
scream for me.

00:36:52.529 --> 00:36:55.508
"Don't keep walking, Pastor."

00:36:55.508 --> 00:36:59.779
You see what comes after.

00:36:59.779 --> 00:37:02.339
That's why Peter said, "Repent."

00:37:02.339 --> 00:37:03.728
Did you notice that word in the text?

00:37:03.728 --> 00:37:05.089
He said, "Repent.

00:37:05.089 --> 00:37:06.089
Turn around.

00:37:06.089 --> 00:37:07.698
You're going the wrong way.

00:37:07.698 --> 00:37:09.768
You have your faith in the law.

00:37:09.768 --> 00:37:12.728
You listened to the prophets, but you missed
the Messiah.

00:37:12.728 --> 00:37:13.728
Repent."

00:37:13.728 --> 00:37:18.349
You're trusting in your works, but you have
to receive this gospel by grace.

00:37:18.349 --> 00:37:19.349
Repent.

00:37:19.349 --> 00:37:24.228
You're living your life for sinful pleasures,
and sin is fun for a season.

00:37:24.228 --> 00:37:33.018
I said, "Sin is fun for a season," emphasis
on season, but after that season comes another

00:37:33.018 --> 00:37:34.549
season.

00:37:34.549 --> 00:37:36.809
Some people who are trying to warn you right
now…

00:37:36.809 --> 00:37:37.809
You tune them out.

00:37:37.809 --> 00:37:38.809
You tell them no.

00:37:38.809 --> 00:37:39.809
You don't want to repent.

00:37:39.809 --> 00:37:41.309
You don't want to hear that.

00:37:41.309 --> 00:37:44.718
But how can the refreshing come if the repentance
doesn't?

00:37:44.718 --> 00:37:45.718
Repent!

00:37:45.718 --> 00:37:47.268
Turn around.

00:37:47.268 --> 00:37:49.819
You have time.

00:37:49.819 --> 00:37:51.688
You're not dead.

00:37:51.688 --> 00:37:52.688
You're still breathing.

00:37:52.688 --> 00:37:54.319
You're not in this forever.

00:37:54.319 --> 00:37:55.369
Let me show you how I know.

00:37:55.369 --> 00:37:57.339
Can I show you how I know it's not forever?

00:37:57.339 --> 00:37:58.978
Can I show you how I know you still have time?

00:37:58.978 --> 00:38:01.609
Can I show you how I know it's not too late?

00:38:01.609 --> 00:38:03.859
Can I show you how I know it's going to turn
around?

00:38:03.859 --> 00:38:07.059
Can I show you why I have faith to preach
this word to you today?

00:38:07.059 --> 00:38:11.819
Because of what Peter said in verse 15.

00:38:11.819 --> 00:38:14.049
Verse 15 is so anointed.

00:38:14.049 --> 00:38:20.379
If you need to share Jesus with somebody,
but you only have five seconds, read them

00:38:20.379 --> 00:38:21.428
Acts 3:15.

00:38:21.428 --> 00:38:22.988
Don't start with Abraham.

00:38:22.988 --> 00:38:24.029
You'll mess it up.

00:38:24.029 --> 00:38:28.748
You'll be putting Abraham on the ark and Moses
and all that, but don't do that.

00:38:28.748 --> 00:38:34.859
Just say Acts 3:15 and show them this.

00:38:34.859 --> 00:38:40.198
He said, "You killed the author of life…"

00:38:40.198 --> 00:38:45.138
Remember, this is AS Peter, not BS Peter.

00:38:45.138 --> 00:38:50.248
Peter was cussing while Jesus was dying, but
now he has been forgiven, and he has repented,

00:38:50.248 --> 00:38:53.279
and he knows that wasn't the end.

00:38:53.279 --> 00:38:58.258
He's looking right at these people and saying,
"When you handed him over to the Romans, you

00:38:58.258 --> 00:38:59.299
killed him.

00:38:59.299 --> 00:39:02.879
When you wanted to give up Barabbas, as was
the custom, instead of the author of life,

00:39:02.879 --> 00:39:05.579
you killed the author."

00:39:05.579 --> 00:39:12.448
You're like, "Pastor, I really want to go
here with you, but this does not feel to me

00:39:12.448 --> 00:39:22.039
like the best verse I should share with my
friends like you just said."

00:39:22.039 --> 00:39:26.199
Why are you stopping at the comma?

00:39:26.199 --> 00:39:28.178
Any English teachers in the room?

00:39:28.178 --> 00:39:32.958
English teachers make some noise!

00:39:32.958 --> 00:39:38.829
Y'all don't get shouted out much, do you?

00:39:38.829 --> 00:39:41.228
I shouted out the basketball players.

00:39:41.228 --> 00:39:42.329
Everybody was happy.

00:39:42.329 --> 00:39:43.718
English teachers!

00:39:43.718 --> 00:39:46.079
I need both of y'all to preach this message.

00:39:46.079 --> 00:39:48.049
This is an all-inclusive gospel.

00:39:48.049 --> 00:39:51.049
I need everybody's help here.

00:39:51.049 --> 00:39:52.599
Tell me what a comma means.

00:39:52.599 --> 00:39:53.599
Stop?

00:39:53.599 --> 00:39:55.589
It means stop?

00:39:55.589 --> 00:39:57.089
Hold on.

00:39:57.089 --> 00:40:03.389
I'm confused, because it sounds like you're
saying, "Pause," but what I see people do

00:40:03.389 --> 00:40:07.238
all the time is get a divorce and stop.

00:40:07.238 --> 00:40:10.718
What I see people do all the time is fail
and stop.

00:40:10.718 --> 00:40:14.559
What I see people do all the time is come
up short and stop.

00:40:14.559 --> 00:40:18.218
What I see people do all the time is try to
change and stop.

00:40:18.218 --> 00:40:21.779
What I see people do all the time is give
it three days and stop.

00:40:21.779 --> 00:40:26.139
Don't ever let that Devil put a period where
God put a comma, because that comma doesn't

00:40:26.139 --> 00:40:27.139
mean it's over!

00:40:27.139 --> 00:40:44.138
It means take a breath and keep going, because
whatever is on the other side of that problem…

00:40:44.138 --> 00:40:48.478
I feel it in my spirit.

00:40:48.478 --> 00:40:56.089
I'm not preaching from my head; I'm preaching
from my heart.

00:40:56.089 --> 00:41:01.069
"This is emotionalism."

00:41:01.069 --> 00:41:03.218
No, it's grammar.

00:41:03.218 --> 00:41:06.899
It is grammar.

00:41:06.899 --> 00:41:09.768
Professor Furtick is in the house.

00:41:09.768 --> 00:41:13.748
Put it back up.

00:41:13.748 --> 00:41:14.748
I'm not done with it yet.

00:41:14.748 --> 00:41:16.358
This sentence is so anointed.

00:41:16.358 --> 00:41:18.799
No, not that…the verse.

00:41:18.799 --> 00:41:20.029
The same verse, y'all.

00:41:20.029 --> 00:41:21.228
Put it up.

00:41:21.228 --> 00:41:25.399
Put it on the screen, please.

00:41:25.399 --> 00:41:26.718
Please!

00:41:26.718 --> 00:41:31.458
This is like us waiting on God.

00:41:31.458 --> 00:41:32.458
You know what I'm saying?

00:41:32.458 --> 00:41:37.238
This is like Abraham…25 years between when
God gave him the promise and he saw it come

00:41:37.238 --> 00:41:38.238
to pass.

00:41:38.238 --> 00:41:41.029
But just because I had to pause doesn't mean
I stop preaching.

00:41:41.029 --> 00:41:54.349
I'm going to stay right here until that word
comes!

00:41:54.349 --> 00:42:00.748
Spirit of the Nature Boys…Charlotte, North
Carolina, where we speak English, Southern

00:42:00.748 --> 00:42:01.859
English.

00:42:01.859 --> 00:42:05.968
I failed Greek.

00:42:05.968 --> 00:42:07.268
I never passed Hebrew.

00:42:07.268 --> 00:42:10.069
They just sent me the degree to get me off
the books.

00:42:10.069 --> 00:42:11.398
That's true.

00:42:11.398 --> 00:42:13.508
I made friends with the professor.

00:42:13.508 --> 00:42:17.158
I said, "Do you really want me to keep taking
your class?"

00:42:17.158 --> 00:42:18.968
I had a degree a couple of weeks later.

00:42:18.968 --> 00:42:22.158
I don't know what happened in between, but
I know what came after.

00:42:22.158 --> 00:42:25.549
I got that cemetery degree.

00:42:25.549 --> 00:42:33.549
"You killed the author."

00:42:33.549 --> 00:42:36.498
I normally give you one word from God.

00:42:36.498 --> 00:42:38.168
Today I give you two.

00:42:38.168 --> 00:42:39.589
You don't need to know Hebrew.

00:42:39.589 --> 00:42:40.819
You don't need to know Greek.

00:42:40.819 --> 00:42:43.218
You don't need to remember Theophilus.

00:42:43.218 --> 00:42:44.238
You don't have to go back to Abraham.

00:42:44.238 --> 00:42:48.139
You don't have to do any of that.

00:42:48.139 --> 00:42:53.258
Those two words that come after the comma…

00:42:53.258 --> 00:43:00.978
That's what I want you to remember for every
battle in your life in this season, for every

00:43:00.978 --> 00:43:05.728
cross in your life in this season, for every
struggle in your life in this season, for

00:43:05.728 --> 00:43:09.198
every setback in your life, for every question
in your life, for every unanswered prayer

00:43:09.198 --> 00:43:14.109
in your life in this season, for every thorn
in your flesh in this season, for every limp

00:43:14.109 --> 00:43:15.829
in your hip this season.

00:43:15.829 --> 00:43:23.148
I want you to remember what comes after the
comma.

00:43:23.148 --> 00:43:27.049
"But God…"

00:43:27.049 --> 00:43:34.388
The only two words you need to whip the Devil's
butt.

00:43:34.388 --> 00:43:38.829
Tell him, "But…"

00:43:38.829 --> 00:43:42.618
Stop being so reactive to the Enemy's attack.

00:43:42.618 --> 00:43:45.128
I told you last week, "Close your doors."

00:43:45.128 --> 00:43:48.768
Now I'm telling you this week, "Cover your
butt."

00:43:48.768 --> 00:43:57.518
Can y'all believe I think about stuff like
this while you're at work?

00:43:57.518 --> 00:44:00.299
"But God…"

00:44:00.299 --> 00:44:06.849
You could do a whole study on every time it
says, "But God" in the Bible, and you'd be

00:44:06.849 --> 00:44:08.589
blessed.

00:44:08.589 --> 00:44:14.799
You'd find out that very rarely will one die
for even a righteous person, but God demonstrates

00:44:14.799 --> 00:44:19.458
his own love for us in this, that while we
were still sinners…

00:44:19.458 --> 00:44:22.149
Not at the end of the movie when we get our
act together.

00:44:22.149 --> 00:44:27.799
Not when we get to heaven one day and we are
given our wings and our trumpets, but while

00:44:27.799 --> 00:44:29.878
I'm still in my sin.

00:44:29.878 --> 00:44:32.069
I need somebody to hear that.

00:44:32.069 --> 00:44:37.089
It is in the midst of the sin that the love
is revealed.

00:44:37.089 --> 00:44:41.069
Don't keep sinning just because of that, but
don't you stop because you're caught up in

00:44:41.069 --> 00:44:42.958
a comma.

00:44:42.958 --> 00:44:44.008
That is a comma.

00:44:44.008 --> 00:44:49.069
It does not mean stop, and it means what's
coming next you need to pay attention to.

00:44:49.069 --> 00:44:50.198
But…

00:44:50.198 --> 00:44:52.478
Tell me if I'm right, English teacher.

00:44:52.478 --> 00:44:55.668
But can be an adverb.

00:44:55.668 --> 00:45:04.909
But can be a preposition.

00:45:04.909 --> 00:45:11.608
In this particular instance, but is not a
noun, so you don't have to get off your butt,

00:45:11.608 --> 00:45:12.659
not in this instance.

00:45:12.659 --> 00:45:13.659
That's a different thing.

00:45:13.659 --> 00:45:18.148
This but (this is important) is a conjunction.

00:45:18.148 --> 00:45:22.779
I remember it because of the song "Conjunction
junction, what's your…"

00:45:22.779 --> 00:45:23.779
Right, right.

00:45:23.779 --> 00:45:31.978
Y'all don't know the Bible, but y'all knew
that.

00:45:31.978 --> 00:45:36.299
I love it.

00:45:36.299 --> 00:45:37.918
Right there in that but is your breakthrough.

00:45:37.918 --> 00:45:39.508
Right there in that but is your freedom.

00:45:39.508 --> 00:45:43.008
Right there in that but is you knowing how
to calm yourself down when you feel like you're

00:45:43.008 --> 00:45:44.309
going crazy.

00:45:44.309 --> 00:45:45.309
But.

00:45:45.309 --> 00:45:47.539
It is a conjunction.

00:45:47.539 --> 00:45:52.289
It is an adversative conjunction.

00:45:52.289 --> 00:46:00.688
What that means is whatever comes after this
but…

00:46:00.688 --> 00:46:05.738
I'm preaching to you today about what comes
after.

00:46:05.738 --> 00:46:16.218
A conjunction that is after this comma means
that whatever comes after this but is going

00:46:16.218 --> 00:46:25.948
to make whatever came before it wish it had
never even happened.

00:46:25.948 --> 00:46:29.158
Let me say it again.

00:46:29.158 --> 00:46:31.289
This is where the deep Christians are.

00:46:31.289 --> 00:46:33.149
Let me say it on this side.

00:46:33.149 --> 00:46:35.569
Or maybe I should say it to this side.

00:46:35.569 --> 00:46:38.839
Or maybe I should say it to this side.

00:46:38.839 --> 00:46:43.099
Or maybe I should say it to the people who
got here early and got a seat right there

00:46:43.099 --> 00:46:44.139
on the floor.

00:46:44.139 --> 00:46:45.139
Okay.

00:46:45.139 --> 00:46:46.139
Maybe it's over here.

00:46:46.139 --> 00:46:47.139
Watch this.

00:46:47.139 --> 00:46:54.079
Whatever comes after this but is going to
cancel out whatever happened before it.

00:46:54.079 --> 00:46:56.968
You didn't hear me.

00:46:56.968 --> 00:47:00.549
It's not going to make it that it never happened.

00:47:00.549 --> 00:47:06.448
It's going to make it that even though it
happened, something greater happened after

00:47:06.448 --> 00:47:13.508
that made what happened before the but…

00:47:13.508 --> 00:47:25.779
I'm preaching on my punctuation marks today!

00:47:25.779 --> 00:47:33.829
When people say to you stuff like, "No offense,
but…"

00:47:33.829 --> 00:47:41.598
Whatever they're getting ready to say on the
other side of that but is going to make you

00:47:41.598 --> 00:47:46.688
forget and disbelieve whatever they said before
it.

00:47:46.688 --> 00:47:53.059
"No offense, but you can't dance, and your
tattoo is crooked, and I don't like your jewelry,

00:47:53.059 --> 00:47:54.848
and you smell weird around your neck."

00:47:54.848 --> 00:47:56.688
You know, whatever they tell you.

00:47:56.688 --> 00:47:59.089
It's going to be so crazy.

00:47:59.089 --> 00:48:01.779
"No offense, but…"

00:48:01.779 --> 00:48:02.779
You get it.

00:48:02.779 --> 00:48:06.648
"Don't take this personally, but…"

00:48:06.648 --> 00:48:11.139
A lady told Holly one time, "Don't take this
personally, but we're leaving the church.

00:48:11.139 --> 00:48:15.649
We don't think Pastor Steven preaches sound
doctrine or the gospel of Jesus Christ.

00:48:15.649 --> 00:48:18.988
We're just tired of seeing people come into
church who are coming in high from the night

00:48:18.988 --> 00:48:19.988
before."

00:48:19.988 --> 00:48:20.988
I couldn't understand.

00:48:20.988 --> 00:48:24.031
If they can't come to church high from the
night before, how are we going to lead them

00:48:24.031 --> 00:48:26.428
to the Most High God they don't even know
about?

00:48:26.428 --> 00:48:27.428
If I can't preach to them…

00:48:27.428 --> 00:48:32.049
How am I going to preach if they don't hear?

00:48:32.049 --> 00:48:41.069
She had the unmitigated nerve, gall, and audacity
to say, "Don't take it personally."

00:48:41.069 --> 00:48:45.988
"Nothing personal, but your church sucks and
you're leading people to hell.

00:48:45.988 --> 00:48:47.418
But it's not personal."

00:48:47.418 --> 00:48:49.329
No, of course not.

00:48:49.329 --> 00:48:51.639
What you said after but…

00:48:51.639 --> 00:48:55.359
"You killed the author…"

00:48:55.359 --> 00:48:58.629
But you can't do that, can you?

00:48:58.629 --> 00:49:05.358
The author is the one who gets to decide when
it's over.

00:49:05.358 --> 00:49:07.829
You can't really kill the author, can you?

00:49:07.829 --> 00:49:10.958
If you kill the author, they can write a sequel.

00:49:10.958 --> 00:49:14.118
If you kill the author, they can put a comma.

00:49:14.118 --> 00:49:19.458
If you kill the author, they can write another
chapter.

00:49:19.458 --> 00:49:21.928
I wasn't shouting over the comma.

00:49:21.928 --> 00:49:24.638
I wasn't shouting over the but.

00:49:24.638 --> 00:49:30.529
I was shouting over what came after.

00:49:30.529 --> 00:49:32.589
I wasn't shouting over the pain.

00:49:32.589 --> 00:49:34.579
I wasn't shouting over the shame.

00:49:34.579 --> 00:49:39.118
I was shouting over what came after.

00:49:39.118 --> 00:49:44.678
If whatever comes after that comma and that
but is bigger than what came before it, and

00:49:44.678 --> 00:49:47.188
what came after that but was God…

00:49:47.188 --> 00:49:52.478
We're talking about the God of Abraham, the
God of Isaac, the God of Jacob.

00:49:52.478 --> 00:49:54.188
I wish Peter would have kept going.

00:49:54.188 --> 00:50:00.529
I wish he would have started talking about
Joseph, because Joseph talked just like this.

00:50:00.529 --> 00:50:01.958
This is how Joseph talked.

00:50:01.958 --> 00:50:02.958
Remember?

00:50:02.958 --> 00:50:08.888
Sold into slavery, left in a pit, taken to
a prison, falsely accused, forgotten in a

00:50:08.888 --> 00:50:14.569
prison, standing before his brothers 39 years
later…

00:50:14.569 --> 00:50:15.678
Forty years of interval.

00:50:15.678 --> 00:50:16.678
That's what you live in.

00:50:16.678 --> 00:50:21.399
You live in the interval, the interval between
what God spoke and what you see.

00:50:21.399 --> 00:50:24.049
You have to believe it in the interval.

00:50:24.049 --> 00:50:26.268
Joseph, after all that time…

00:50:26.268 --> 00:50:29.768
I have to show you what he said.

00:50:29.768 --> 00:50:30.969
Peter stopped one character short.

00:50:30.969 --> 00:50:45.958
He should have talked about Joseph who said,
"As for you, you intended to harm me…"

00:50:45.958 --> 00:50:49.698
You'll hear Joseph as Peter is preaching about
Jesus.

00:50:49.698 --> 00:50:51.779
Remember what Peter just said.

00:50:51.779 --> 00:50:56.799
"You killed him, but the grave couldn't keep
him."

00:50:56.799 --> 00:51:01.718
Let me be explicit.

00:51:01.718 --> 00:51:04.978
Your faith can't be in the miracle.

00:51:04.978 --> 00:51:07.059
It has to be in the man.

00:51:07.059 --> 00:51:08.698
It has to be in Jesus.

00:51:08.698 --> 00:51:09.889
It has to be in what he did.

00:51:09.889 --> 00:51:13.369
I'm talking about the fact that he got up
out of the grave.

00:51:13.369 --> 00:51:15.289
That's the basis of our faith.

00:51:15.289 --> 00:51:17.049
His name is Jesus.

00:51:17.049 --> 00:51:19.779
His name will still be Jesus if I have a job.

00:51:19.779 --> 00:51:22.448
His name will still be Jesus if I don't have
a job.

00:51:22.448 --> 00:51:24.718
His name will still be Jesus if I'm crying.

00:51:24.718 --> 00:51:27.768
His name will still be Jesus if I lose 20
or if I gain 20.

00:51:27.768 --> 00:51:29.779
His name will still be Jesus if you like me.

00:51:29.779 --> 00:51:30.958
His name will still be Jesus.

00:51:30.958 --> 00:51:37.258
That's not changing, so neither is my faith.

00:51:37.258 --> 00:51:41.309
He got up.

00:51:41.309 --> 00:51:46.968
It was cross versus Creator, and guess who
won.

00:51:46.968 --> 00:51:51.529
It was God versus grave, and guess who gave
up.

00:51:51.529 --> 00:51:53.738
Guess who tapped out.

00:51:53.738 --> 00:51:56.919
Not God.

00:51:56.919 --> 00:51:58.718
So why would you?

00:51:58.718 --> 00:52:04.069
Joseph, looking at all his pain and all his
trauma, said something so powerful, and you

00:52:04.069 --> 00:52:05.928
will recognize it.

00:52:05.928 --> 00:52:10.898
You will wonder if Peter was plagiarizing
Joseph when he said, "You killed the author,

00:52:10.898 --> 00:52:11.898
but God…"

00:52:11.898 --> 00:52:12.898
Look at this Scripture.

00:52:12.898 --> 00:52:14.168
This is amazing.

00:52:14.168 --> 00:52:19.348
"You intended to harm me, but God…"

00:52:19.348 --> 00:52:23.768
Do you recognize those two words?

00:52:23.768 --> 00:52:26.678
Do you recognize that conjunction?

00:52:26.678 --> 00:52:29.968
The same one Jesus was doing on the cross
Joseph was doing in his relationships.

00:52:29.968 --> 00:52:33.039
That's what you have to do.

00:52:33.039 --> 00:52:38.878
He said, "You intended to harm me…"

00:52:38.878 --> 00:52:41.238
Harm me.

00:52:41.238 --> 00:52:42.579
I can't change that.

00:52:42.579 --> 00:52:47.728
"…but God intended it for what is now being
done."

00:52:47.728 --> 00:52:57.988
He lived 55 more years to see his children's
children's children brought to his knees.

00:52:57.988 --> 00:52:59.049
That's amazing.

00:52:59.049 --> 00:53:03.358
All because of what happened after the comma.

00:53:03.358 --> 00:53:07.488
The Lord sent me prophetically to speak to
somebody who's at the comma right now.

00:53:07.488 --> 00:53:09.569
"What am I going to do next?

00:53:09.569 --> 00:53:11.108
How am I going to handle this?

00:53:11.108 --> 00:53:12.549
Can I get up from the fall?

00:53:12.549 --> 00:53:14.069
Are we going to try it again?

00:53:14.069 --> 00:53:15.458
Are we going to believe again?

00:53:15.458 --> 00:53:17.958
Am I going to get out of the bed before 11:00
a.m. this week?

00:53:17.958 --> 00:53:20.829
What am I going to do next?"

00:53:20.829 --> 00:53:26.138
Joseph shows us that you don't need a deep
revelation.

00:53:26.138 --> 00:53:37.918
You just need to disrupt the Devil with a
but, because what comes after that but…

00:53:37.918 --> 00:53:39.279
It doesn't change the past.

00:53:39.279 --> 00:53:54.878
No, you can't change it, but what comes after
can change the very nature of the whole first

00:53:54.878 --> 00:54:00.779
two hours of the movie, of the whole first
20 years of your life, of the last 20 years

00:54:00.779 --> 00:54:01.779
of your life.

00:54:01.779 --> 00:54:03.579
What comes after.

00:54:03.579 --> 00:54:06.299
You'll be turning around, saying, "Now wait
a minute.

00:54:06.299 --> 00:54:08.879
Maybe God allowed some of that.

00:54:08.879 --> 00:54:11.208
Maybe it wasn't bad.

00:54:11.208 --> 00:54:16.588
Maybe God put me through that test so I would
have a testimony."

00:54:16.588 --> 00:54:20.069
Maybe God let Joseph be in that pit so he
could be standing in that position to be a

00:54:20.069 --> 00:54:21.109
provider.

00:54:21.109 --> 00:54:25.389
You have to believe that by faith.

00:54:25.389 --> 00:54:30.619
"But God…"

00:54:30.619 --> 00:54:33.928
Don't tell me you don't know how to fight
the Devil this week, and don't tell me you

00:54:33.928 --> 00:54:35.358
don't have any weapons.

00:54:35.358 --> 00:54:39.238
You don't need a big one if it's loaded.

00:54:39.238 --> 00:54:43.779
That is a loaded statement, because that but
God…

00:54:43.779 --> 00:54:44.779
Anything.

00:54:44.779 --> 00:54:45.779
Loneliness.

00:54:45.779 --> 00:54:47.049
"I feel alone."

00:54:47.049 --> 00:54:52.128
I know you do, but God is with me.

00:54:52.128 --> 00:54:54.998
And if God is with me, he's going to bring
everything I need.

00:54:54.998 --> 00:54:59.829
I can't do it, but God is in me.

00:54:59.829 --> 00:55:01.248
But God's Spirit…

00:55:01.248 --> 00:55:03.488
Peter couldn't preach until the Spirit came.

00:55:03.488 --> 00:55:06.629
It was what came after.

00:55:06.629 --> 00:55:08.599
I declare a shift in your life.

00:55:08.599 --> 00:55:10.658
I declare a shift in your self-image.

00:55:10.658 --> 00:55:12.909
I declare a shift in your insecurities.

00:55:12.909 --> 00:55:15.088
I declare a shift in your adversity.

00:55:15.088 --> 00:55:17.748
I declare a shift in your perspective.

00:55:17.748 --> 00:55:23.948
You cannot change the past, but God can change
your perspective.

00:55:23.948 --> 00:55:28.049
"You tried to harm me.

00:55:28.049 --> 00:55:29.099
It came to harm me.

00:55:29.099 --> 00:55:30.838
I even harmed myself."

00:55:30.838 --> 00:55:32.539
The word harm…

00:55:32.539 --> 00:55:38.079
It says, "Harm."

00:55:38.079 --> 00:55:44.368
Can I change it?

00:55:44.368 --> 00:55:46.299
I don't want to erase it, but can I change
it?

00:55:46.299 --> 00:55:47.299
I can't erase it.

00:55:47.299 --> 00:55:48.299
It's up there.

00:55:48.299 --> 00:55:49.299
Can I change it?

00:55:49.299 --> 00:56:05.468
Of course you can…by what comes after.

00:56:05.468 --> 00:56:12.539
I feel like David Blaine up here, y'all.

00:56:12.539 --> 00:56:15.508
That was magic.

00:56:15.508 --> 00:56:19.319
How we took something so ugly…

00:56:19.319 --> 00:56:20.609
What came after?

00:56:20.609 --> 00:56:21.728
Three letters.

00:56:21.728 --> 00:56:22.728
Three days.

00:56:22.728 --> 00:56:24.289
"You killed the author.

00:56:24.289 --> 00:56:30.309
You killed the composer, but it didn't stop
the symphony."

00:56:30.309 --> 00:56:34.968
God is the one who brings it all into harmony.

00:56:34.968 --> 00:56:37.329
Harmony.

00:56:37.329 --> 00:56:38.968
That's a musical term.

00:56:38.968 --> 00:56:42.398
Holly has a book club, but I have a songwriting
team.

00:56:42.398 --> 00:56:43.428
Harmony.

00:56:43.428 --> 00:56:46.448
The author, the composer…

00:56:46.448 --> 00:56:48.368
They get to write the notes, see.

00:56:48.368 --> 00:56:50.448
Y'all, I don't play piano.

00:56:50.448 --> 00:56:56.398
I play guitar pretty good, not as good as
Joey.

00:56:56.398 --> 00:56:59.188
Who does play guitar as good as Joey?

00:56:59.188 --> 00:57:07.938
But I'll tell you right now I know how to
find middle C on this piano.

00:57:07.938 --> 00:57:14.159
I wanted to show you what Joseph meant when
he said, "You meant to harm me, but God used

00:57:14.159 --> 00:57:17.018
all of it to bring us to this moment."

00:57:17.018 --> 00:57:27.758
I will not let what happened before regulate
what I believe God for going forward.

00:57:27.758 --> 00:57:39.678
I use that as an illustration, church, just
to talk to you about the fact that this note,

00:57:39.678 --> 00:57:44.238
this single note in isolation…

00:57:44.238 --> 00:57:46.668
Is it a good note?

00:57:46.668 --> 00:57:55.458
Anybody who thinks it's a good note, make
some noise for middle C. Or is it a bad note?

00:57:55.458 --> 00:57:57.688
Everybody who thinks it's a bad note, make
some noise.

00:57:57.688 --> 00:58:02.608
"Boo, middle C." Come on.

00:58:02.608 --> 00:58:07.079
You know intuitively what I'm trying to teach
you.

00:58:07.079 --> 00:58:10.698
You know intuitively what Miles Davis said.

00:58:10.698 --> 00:58:19.148
He said, "It is not the note you play that
is wrong.

00:58:19.148 --> 00:58:28.559
It is the next note you play that makes it
wrong or right."

00:58:28.559 --> 00:58:31.309
There's nothing wrong with that note.

00:58:31.309 --> 00:58:33.678
There's nothing right with that note.

00:58:33.678 --> 00:58:35.398
Is it good?

00:58:35.398 --> 00:58:37.438
Is it bad?

00:58:37.438 --> 00:58:39.279
Is it neither?

00:58:39.279 --> 00:58:52.839
It's neither until I hear what comes after.

00:58:52.839 --> 00:58:55.398
Bad note.

00:58:55.398 --> 00:58:57.388
Same note.

00:58:57.388 --> 00:59:00.198
Next note.

00:59:00.198 --> 00:59:07.868
Not a bad note, but it's a dissonant note
because the interval is dissonant.

00:59:07.868 --> 00:59:09.228
There's nothing wrong with this note.

00:59:09.228 --> 00:59:12.948
Don't start running around all of your pianos
in your house and taking out middle C. "Oh,

00:59:12.948 --> 00:59:14.178
it's a bad note."

00:59:14.178 --> 00:59:15.428
This is what we want to do.

00:59:15.428 --> 00:59:16.428
Something happens in our life.

00:59:16.428 --> 00:59:17.428
"I've got to get rid of that stress.

00:59:17.428 --> 00:59:18.428
I've got to get rid of that challenge.

00:59:18.428 --> 00:59:19.428
I've got to get rid of that thing.

00:59:19.428 --> 00:59:20.428
This is bad.

00:59:20.428 --> 00:59:21.428
This is horrible."

00:59:21.428 --> 00:59:22.428
No, no, no.

00:59:22.428 --> 00:59:29.658
You don't know yet until you hear…

00:59:29.658 --> 00:59:45.399
It sounds like Jaws in here right now.

00:59:45.399 --> 00:59:52.809
God brought us here to talk about your next
note, because you can't control so much of

00:59:52.809 --> 00:59:54.938
what happens.

00:59:54.938 --> 00:59:58.529
You can't erase what you did.

00:59:58.529 --> 01:00:06.508
Peter said, "You killed the author, but God…"

01:00:06.508 --> 01:00:14.329
Do you really think anything you've done is
greater than who God is?

01:00:14.329 --> 01:00:24.508
Do you really think any mistake you've made
is greater than who God is?

01:00:24.508 --> 01:00:32.248
Joseph said, "You meant to harm me, but God
who works all things together for his good

01:00:32.248 --> 01:00:42.638
will take what was meant to harm me and bring
it into harmony."

01:00:42.638 --> 01:00:44.398
Next note.

01:00:44.398 --> 01:00:47.748
It's your next note that God wants to speak
about.

01:00:47.748 --> 01:00:51.408
That sounds good.

01:00:51.408 --> 01:00:52.809
Middle C has been redeemed.

01:00:52.809 --> 01:01:00.849
All I had to do was put it with F. That interval
is called a perfect fourth.

01:01:00.849 --> 01:01:03.888
English, music theory, therapy…

01:01:03.888 --> 01:01:09.299
Y'all ought to start paying me.

01:01:09.299 --> 01:01:16.588
When I put that together…

01:01:16.588 --> 01:01:21.478
We could do a lot with that.

01:01:21.478 --> 01:01:37.678
"This is my story…"

01:01:37.678 --> 01:01:52.178
It's the same note I started with and did
this to you, but where I took it next…

01:01:52.178 --> 01:01:58.139
What is your next note?

01:01:58.139 --> 01:02:05.708
Or are you going to stay stuck on middle C
forever?

01:02:05.708 --> 01:02:08.138
Now we need a next note.

01:02:08.138 --> 01:02:13.958
"This is my story…"

01:02:13.958 --> 01:02:18.658
Within a story.

01:02:18.658 --> 01:02:20.629
God is the author.

01:02:20.629 --> 01:02:23.198
The Devil is a liar.

01:02:23.198 --> 01:02:24.799
He is defeated.

01:02:24.799 --> 01:02:30.059
He killed the author, but God has raised him.

01:02:30.059 --> 01:02:35.228
Oh, what's your next note going to be?

01:02:35.228 --> 01:02:39.619
"This is my story…"

01:02:39.619 --> 01:02:41.908
The Devil is not the author.

01:02:41.908 --> 01:02:43.908
You're not the author.

01:02:43.908 --> 01:02:46.799
God is the author.

01:02:46.799 --> 01:02:50.508
Don't you want to see what's on the other
side of this but?

01:02:50.508 --> 01:02:53.448
Or are you going to die at the comma?

01:02:53.448 --> 01:02:55.319
Are you going to die at the gate?

01:02:55.319 --> 01:02:57.588
Are you going to die in the disappointment?

01:02:57.588 --> 01:02:59.258
Yes, people broke your heart.

01:02:59.258 --> 01:03:00.888
That's what brokenhearted people do.

01:03:00.888 --> 01:03:14.178
They meant to harm you, but God…

01:03:14.178 --> 01:03:20.319
What is your next note?

01:03:20.319 --> 01:03:22.139
God says you get to choose.

01:03:22.139 --> 01:03:24.619
"Are you going to play the one I wrote for
you?

01:03:24.619 --> 01:03:28.660
Are you going to play the one I destined for
you?

01:03:28.660 --> 01:03:37.829
Are you going to play the one I created you
for so that you have a story?"

01:03:37.829 --> 01:03:41.388
You could be telling a different story this
time next year.

01:03:41.388 --> 01:03:45.128
It's about the next note.

01:03:45.128 --> 01:03:47.448
Come off that cross.

01:03:47.448 --> 01:03:49.559
Come out of that grave.

01:03:49.559 --> 01:03:51.658
Come out of that failure.

01:03:51.658 --> 01:03:53.829
Repent and turn to the Lord.

01:03:53.829 --> 01:04:01.488
He brought you here for this moment to tell
you he is the author and the finisher, and

01:04:01.488 --> 01:04:08.438
the next note is yours to sing.

01:04:08.438 --> 01:04:14.799
"Amazing grace…"

01:04:14.799 --> 01:04:17.978
See?

01:04:17.978 --> 01:04:24.338
"…how sweet…"

01:04:24.338 --> 01:04:27.518
No.

01:04:27.518 --> 01:04:30.698
No.

01:04:30.698 --> 01:04:37.059
"Amazing grace…"

01:04:37.059 --> 01:04:38.248
It's your note.

01:04:38.248 --> 01:04:46.968
"…how sweet the sound that saved…"

01:04:46.968 --> 01:04:48.799
Next note.

01:04:48.799 --> 01:04:56.159
"…a wretch like me.

01:04:56.159 --> 01:05:04.898
I once was lost, but now…"

01:05:04.898 --> 01:05:06.309
Next note.

01:05:06.309 --> 01:05:11.539
